@nerdy_nettie hi! I am the creator and pioneer of the process of healing that is part of being a sexuality doula, so currently there is no one else that does what I do. my long term dream is to create a certification program to teach others how to become sexuality doulas as well. for now, though, it’s just me and unfortunately I am not taking any new clients for 2019). however, if you’re looking bring some healing and liberation to your sexuality and want someone in your area, check out @theaasect’s directory and find a sexuality professional (therapists, educators, coaches) in your area. 🧡
@nerdy_nettie I forgot to mention! I work with clients all over the world via Skype, so you living in a small town would not be an issue if we were ever to work together.

Photo by Ev’Yan Whitney • she/they on August 15, 2019. Image may contain: possible text that says 'and femmes seeking freedom from shame and fear in order achieve sexual liberation. With programs that focus primarily on holistic Whitney has become a trailblazer for a growing community looking to develop better relationship their sexuality in way that allows them to feel safe and heard. But, if heard of the "sexuality doula" before, you're not alone. The role is pretty complex, says Whitney, describing it as someone who helps people transition of sexual shame, trauma, fear, and confusion and into sexual liberation, expression, freedom. That's a heavy job.'

Photo by Ev’Yan Whitney • she/they on August 15, 2019. Image may contain: possible text that says 'ability to navigate sexuality. And, breaking through that oppression can be incredibly powerful. "Because that navigating is being done while to connect back into their bodies and heal their trauma and un-shame their sexuality, all kinds things pop up in this process," Whitney continues. "The thing I affirm in them is that that work of sexual liberation and healing is radical act and a giant 'fuck you' to white supremacist patriarchal capitalism. To take up space with our to celebrate our sexuality is an act of resistance.'
